    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">System prompt best practice</span>
      <div class="hero-accent-line"></div>
      <h1>More instructions.<br>Same token budget.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lead">
        Markdown is genuinely great for AI — as output format, and as input when documents are long and token cost isn't critical. But for system prompts the calculus changes: they run on every single request, token overhead compounds, and you want to cram in as many instructions as possible. <em>Plain text formatted (AI-ready)</em> keeps the structure, drops the markup, and gives that space back to meaning.
      </p>
      <div class="stat-strip">
